name: Pig Game
smallText: This is javascript game. It's already an existing social game which one called Pig game. The rule is the same with rules from the RL game. The first turn play player one. He drops cubes and calculate the result. He can drop cubes until he gets the 1. If he gets 1 only on one cube it will lose a turn. But if he role 1 on both cube, it will lose a turn and current score. At any moment it can press the hold button and save the current score. The saved score cannot be lost. After pressing the hold button, player one loses a turn and then NPC play. Who first earns 100 he gets a win.

text.name: p
text.content: This is javascript game. It's already an existing social game which one called Pig game. Here we have a possibility to play this game with a virtual rival, or NPC.

text.name: p
text.content: The rule is the same with rules from the RL game. The first turn play player one. He drops cubes and calculate the result. He can drop cubes until he gets the 1. If he gets 1 only on one cube it will lose a turn. But if he role 1 on both cube, it will lose a turn and current score. At any moment it can press the hold button and save the current score. The saved score cannot be lost. After pressing the hold button, player one loses a turn and then NPC play. Who first earns 100 he gets a win.

text.name: p
text.content: On start, we have to create an account. We do that by clicking on the green cross in the account session. When we create an account we will get 1000$ starting budget for bids. On the left, we have default bets value. It's 100$. Above we got 4 options for making bets size. After we do all this setup, we have to select an account by click on the account name and then click on button play game

text.name: p
text.content: When you create an account, that account will save to local storage. So all your activity is saved. We can play 2,3 games, then turn off and come back after, and play again from where we left off.

text.name: p
text.content: When the game start, we play first turn. On the above left, we have two buttons. One is for roll dice and another one is for hold score. On the above right, we have a timer that measures how long we play.

text.name: p
text.content: Under, in the middle, we have two dice. That is dice which one we rolling.  On the left is two panels.  Upper is our saved score. Under one is the current score. That is score wich one we get from dice in current turn. On the right side is the same but for NPC.

text.name: p
text.content: When we finish and win the game, we will get the message, and after a 3-sec game will redirect to the create game screen. On the end we chack our lose or win money, making another or same bets and play the game again.
